The steps to use WebSocket in a Node.js application are as follows:

1. Install the `ws` library:
 - Run the command `npm install ws`.

2. Create a WebSocket server:
 ```javascript
 const WebSocket = require('ws');
 const server = new WebSocket.Server({ port: 8080 });

 server.on('connection', (socket) => {
 socket.on('message', (message) => {
 console.log(`Received: ${message}`);
 socket.send('Hello from server!');
 });
 });
 ```

3. Connect from client:
 ```javascript
 const socket = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:8080');
 socket.onopen = () => {
 socket.send('Hello from client!');
 };
 socket.onmessage = (event) => {
 console.log(`Received: ${event.data}`);
 };
 ```

Once you complete the above steps, your Node.js application will be able to communicate in real-time via WebSocket.

