The steps to use Axios to call API in Vue.js applications are as follows:

1. Install Axios:
 - Run the command `npm install axios`.

2. Create a service to call API:
 ```javascript
 import axios from 'axios';

 export const apiService = {
 getData() {
 return axios.get('https://api.example.com/data');
 }
 };
 ```

3. Using the service in the component:
 ```javascript
 <template>
 <div>
 <ul>
 <li v-for="item in data" :key="item.id">{{ item.name }}</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 </template>

 <script>
 import { apiService } from './apiService';

 export default {
 data() {
 return {
 data: []
 };
 },
 mounted() {
 apiService.getData().then(response => {
 this.data = response.data;
 });
 }
 };
 </script>
 ```

Once you've completed the above steps, your Vue.js app should be able to fetch data from the API using Axios.

