2. Create a component for displaying paginated data:
   ```bash
   ng generate component paginated-list
   ```

3. Import MatPaginatorModule in your module:
   ```javascript
   import { MatPaginatorModule } from '@angular/material/paginator';
   ```

4. Use MatPaginator in your component template:
   ```html
   <table mat-table [dataSource]='dataSource'>
       <!-- Define columns here -->
   </table>
   <mat-paginator [pageSizeOptions]='[5, 10, 20]'></mat-paginator>
   ```

5. Implement pagination logic in your component:
   ```javascript
   import { MatPaginator } from '@angular/material/paginator';
   import { ViewChild } from '@angular/core';

   export class PaginatedListComponent implements OnInit {
       @ViewChild(MatPaginator) paginator: MatPaginator;
       dataSource = new Mat TableDataSource();

       ngOnInit() {
           this.dataSource.paginator = this.paginator;
           this.loadData();
       }

       loadData() {
           // Load your data here and set it to dataSource.data
       }
   }
   ```

6. Style the paginator:
   - You can customize the paginator's appearance using CSS or Angular Material themes.

Once you've completed these steps, your Angular application will support pagination for displaying large datasets effectively.

