The steps to implement a simple to-do list application using React are as follows:

1. Create a new React application:
   ```bash
   npx create-react-app todo-app
   cd todo-app
   ```

2. Create a ToDo component:
   ```javascript
   import React, { useState } from 'react';

   function ToDo() {
       const [tasks, setTasks] = useState([]);
       const [task, setTask] = useState('');

       const addTask = () => {
           setTasks([...tasks, task]);
           setTask('');
       };

       return (
           <div>
               <input type="text" value={task} onChange={(e) => setTask(e.target.value)} />
               <button onClick={addTask}>Add Task</button>
               <ul>
                   {tasks.map((t, index) => <li key={index}>{t}</li>)}
               </ul>
           </div>
       );
   }
   export default ToDo;
   ```

3. Use the ToDo component in your main App component:
   ```javascript
   import React from 'react';
   import ToDo from './ToDo';

   function App() {
       return (
           <div className="App">
               <h1>To-Do List</h1>
               <ToDo />
           </div>
       );
   }
   export default App;
   ```

4. Run the application:
   - Execute `npm start` to see your to-do list application in action.

Once you've completed these steps, you will have a functional to-do list application built with React.

