Steps to implement server-side pagination in Node.js:

1. Use query parameters to specify the `page` and `limit`:
```javascript
app.get('/items', (req, res) => {
  const page = parseInt(req.query.page) || 1;
  const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit) || 10;
  const skip = (page - 1) * limit;

  // Fetch data with pagination logic
  Item.find().skip(skip).limit(limit).exec((err, items) => {
    res.json(items);
  });
});
```

2. Example request: `/items?page=2&limit=10`

 Reference: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Link

