Steps to configure CORS in an Express.js application:

1. Install the `cors` package:
```bash
npm install cors
```

2. Use CORS middleware in your Express app:
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const cors = require('cors');

const app = express();
app.use(cors()); // Allow all domains by default

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello World!');
});

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server running on port 3000');
});
```

3. To restrict CORS to certain origins, you can configure it:
```javascript
app.use(cors({ origin: 'http://example.com' }));
```

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/cors

