Steps to implement Google OAuth in a Node.js application:

1. Install necessary packages:
```bash
npm install passport passport-google-oauth20 express-session
```

2. Set up Google OAuth credentials on Google Developer Console:
- Go to https://console.developers.google.com/ and create a new project.
- Enable the Google+ API.
- Create OAuth credentials and get the client ID and client secret.

3. Configure Passport with Google OAuth strategy:
```javascript
const passport = require('passport');
const GoogleStrategy = require('passport-google-oauth20').Strategy;

passport.use(new GoogleStrategy({
  clientID: 'YOUR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID',
  clientSecret: 'YOUR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET',
  callbackURL: 'http://localhost:3000/auth/google/callback'
}, (accessToken, refreshToken, profile, done) => {
  return done(null, profile);
}));
```

4. Set up the authentication routes:
```javascript
app.get('/auth/google', passport.authenticate('google', { scope: ['profile', 'email'] }));

app.get('/auth/google/callback', passport.authenticate('google', { failureRedirect: '/' }), (req, res) => {
  res.redirect('/');
});
```

5. Handle user session with `express-session`.

 Reference: https://www.passportjs.org/packages/passport-google-oauth20/

