Steps to set up MongoDB with Mongoose in a Node.js application:

1. Install MongoDB and Mongoose:
```bash
npm install mongoose
```

2. Connect to MongoDB using Mongoose:
```javascript
const mongoose = require('mongoose');

mongoose.connect('mongodb://localhost/myDatabase', {
  useNewUrlParser: true,
  useUnifiedTopology: true
});

mongoose.connection.once('open', () => {
  console.log('MongoDB connected');
});
```

3. Define a Mongoose model:
```javascript
const Schema = mongoose.Schema;

const userSchema = new Schema({
  name: { type: String, required: true },
  email: { type: String, required: true, unique: true }
});

const User = mongoose.model('User', userSchema);
```

4. Create and save a document to the database:
```javascript
const newUser = new User({
  name: 'John Doe',
  email: 'john.doe@example.com'
});

newUser.save().then(() => {
  console.log('User saved');
});
```

5. Query the database to retrieve documents:
```javascript
User.find({}).then(users => {
  console.log(users);
});
```

 Reference: https://mongoosejs.com/docs/

