Steps to implement pagination in a Node.js API:

1. Calculate the page and limit parameters from the query string:
```javascript
const page = parseInt(req.query.page) || 1;
const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit) || 10;
```

2. Calculate the skip value to determine which records to fetch:
```javascript
const skip = (page - 1) * limit;
```

3. Fetch the paginated data from your database using skip and limit:
```javascript
app.get('/api/posts', async (req, res) => {
  const posts = await Post.find().skip(skip).limit(limit);
  res.json(posts);
});
```

4. Return metadata like total pages and current page for client-side handling:
```javascript
const totalPosts = await Post.countDocuments();
const totalPages = Math.ceil(totalPosts / limit);
res.json({ posts, totalPages, currentPage: page });
```

 Reference: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials

