Steps to implement RBAC in a Node.js application:

1. Define user roles (e.g., 'admin', 'user', 'guest').
2. Create a middleware to check the user's role for protected routes:
```javascript
const checkRole = (role) => {
  return (req, res, next) => {
    if (req.user.role !== role) {
      return res.status(403).json({ message: 'Access Denied' });
    }
    next();
  };
};
```

3. Protect routes by using the role-checking middleware:
```javascript
app.post('/admin', checkRole('admin'), (req, res) => {
  res.send('Admin content');
});
```

4. Assign roles to users when they register or authenticate.

 Reference: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials

