Steps to implement session-based authentication in Express.js:

1. Install required packages:
```bash
npm install express-session
```

2. Set up `express-session` middleware:
```javascript
const session = require('express-session');
app.use(session({
  secret: 'your_secret_key',
  resave: false,
  saveUninitialized: true
}));
```

3. Create login route to store user data in session:
```javascript
app.post('/login', (req, res) => {
  const { username } = req.body;
  req.session.user = { username };
  res.send('Logged in');
});
```

4. Create middleware to protect routes:
```javascript
const authMiddleware = (req, res, next) => {
  if (req.session.user) {
    next();
  } else {
    res.status(401).send('Unauthorized');
  }
};
```

5. Use the middleware for protected routes:
```javascript
app.get('/dashboard', authMiddleware, (req, res) => {
  res.send('Welcome to dashboard');
});
```

 Reference: https://expressjs.com/en/resources/middleware/session.html

