Steps to use useEffect in React:

1. Import useEffect from React:
```javascript
import { useEffect } from 'react';
```

2. Use useEffect inside a component:
```javascript
const MyComponent = () => {
  useEffect(() => {
    console.log('Component mounted');
  }, []); // Empty array means it runs only once (on mount)

  return <div>Hello, World!</div>;
};
```

3. Run the effect on component mount, update, or unmount:
```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  console.log('Component updated');
  return () => {
    console.log('Cleanup before unmount');
  };
}, [someDependency]); // Runs on specific state change
```

 Reference: https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-effect.html

