Steps to implement a loading spinner in React:

1. Create a loading spinner component:
```javascript
const LoadingSpinner = () => {
  return <div className='spinner'>Loading...</div>;
};
```

2. Use the spinner in a parent component:
```javascript
const MyComponent = () => {
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);

  useEffect(() => {
    setTimeout(() => {
      setLoading(false);
    }, 3000); // Simulate a loading process
  }, []);

  return (
    <div>
      {loading ? <LoadingSpinner /> : <div>Content loaded!</div>}
    </div>
  );
};
```

3. Style the spinner (CSS):
```css
.spinner {
  border: 4px solid #f3f3f3;
  border-top: 4px solid #3498db;
  border-radius: 50%;
  width: 50px;
  height: 50px;
  animation: spin 2s linear infinite;
}

@keyframes spin {
  0% { transform: rotate(0deg); }
  100% { transform: rotate(360deg); }
}
```

 Reference: https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-state.html

