Steps to implement pagination in React:

1. Define a state to manage the current page:
```javascript
const [currentPage, setCurrentPage] = useState(1);
const itemsPerPage = 10;
```

2. Slice the data based on the current page:
```javascript
const paginatedItems = items.slice((currentPage - 1) * itemsPerPage, currentPage * itemsPerPage);
```

3. Create a function to change the page:
```javascript
const changePage = (page) => {
  setCurrentPage(page);
};
```

4. Render the paginated items and page buttons:
```javascript
const Pagination = () => {
  return (
    <div>
      <ul>
        {paginatedItems.map(item => <li key={item.id}>{item.name}</li>)}
      </ul>
      <button onClick={() => changePage(currentPage - 1)}>Previous</button>
      <button onClick={() => changePage(currentPage + 1)}>Next</button>
    </div>
  );
};
```

 Reference: https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-state.html

