Steps to implement state management in React using Redux:

1. Install Redux and React-Redux:
```bash
npm install redux react-redux
```

2. Create Redux actions and reducers:
```javascript
const ADD_ITEM = 'ADD_ITEM';

const addItem = (item) => ({
  type: ADD_ITEM,
  payload: item,
});

const initialState = [];

const itemReducer = (state = initialState, action) => {
  switch (action.type) {
    case ADD_ITEM:
      return [...state, action.payload];
    default:
      return state;
  }
};
```

3. Create a Redux store and provide it to the application:
```javascript
import { createStore } from 'redux';
import { Provider } from 'react-redux';

const store = createStore(itemReducer);

const App = () => (
  <Provider store={store}>
    <MyComponent />
  </Provider>
);
```

4. Connect Redux state to React components using `useSelector` and `useDispatch`:
```javascript
const MyComponent = () => {
  const items = useSelector((state) => state);
  const dispatch = useDispatch();

  const addItemHandler = () => {
    dispatch(addItem('New item'));
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={addItemHandler}>Add Item</button>
      <ul>{items.map((item, index) => <li key={index}>{item}</li>)}</ul>
    </div>
  );
};
```

 Reference: https://redux.js.org/

