Steps to handle errors in JavaScript using try-catch:

1. Use try-catch block:
```javascript
try {
  // Code that may throw an error
  throw new Error('Something went wrong!');
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Caught an error:', error.message);
}
```

2. You can also include a `finally` block to execute code after try-catch, regardless of whether an error occurred:
```javascript
finally {
  console.log('This will run no matter what');
}
```

 Reference: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/try...catch

