Steps to implement authentication in a Node.js app using Passport:

1. Install Passport and related packages:
```bash
npm install passport passport-local express-session
```

2. Configure Passport for local authentication:
```javascript
const passport = require('passport');
const LocalStrategy = require('passport-local').Strategy;

passport.use(new LocalStrategy((username, password, done) => {
  // Validate user credentials
  done(null, user);
}));
```

3. Use Passport in your Express app:
```javascript
app.use(require('express-session')({ secret: 'your-secret' }));
app.use(passport.initialize());
app.use(passport.session());
```

