Steps to implement JWT authentication in a Node.js app:

1. Install the `jsonwebtoken` package:
```bash
npm install jsonwebtoken
```

2. Generate a JWT when the user logs in:
```javascript
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');
const token = jwt.sign({ userId: user.id }, 'your-secret-key');
```

3. Verify the JWT for protected routes:
```javascript
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  const token = req.header('Authorization');
  if (!token) return res.status(403).send('Access denied');

  jwt.verify(token, 'your-secret-key', (err, decoded) => {
    if (err) return res.status(400).send('Invalid token');
    req.user = decoded;
    next();
  });
});
```

 Reference: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/

