Steps to create a GraphQL API with Apollo Server:

1. Install Apollo Server and GraphQL:
```bash
npm install apollo-server graphql
```

2. Define your GraphQL schema:
```javascript
const { gql } = require('apollo-server');
const typeDefs = gql`
  type Query {
    hello: String
  }
`;
```

3. Set up Apollo Server with your schema and resolvers:
```javascript
const resolvers = {
  Query: {
    hello: () => 'Hello, world!'
  }
};

const { ApolloServer } = require('apollo-server');
const server = new ApolloServer({ typeDefs, resolvers });

server.listen().then(({ url }) => {
  console.log(`Server ready at ${url}`);
});
```

 Reference: https://www.apollographql.com/docs/apollo-server/

