Steps to set up an Nginx server to serve a Node.js app:

1. Install Nginx on your server:
```bash
sudo apt-get install nginx
```

2. Configure Nginx to forward requests to your Node.js app:
```nginx
server {
  listen 80;
  server_name your-domain.com;

  location / {
    proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
  }
}
```

3. Restart Nginx:
```bash
sudo systemctl restart nginx
```

4. Start your Node.js app:
```bash
node app.js
```

 Reference: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-set-up-a-node-js-app-with-nginx-on-ubuntu-18-04

