Steps to set up routing in an Express.js app:

1. Create routes using `app.get`, `app.post`, etc.:
```javascript
app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello, World!');
});
```

2. Organize routes into separate modules for scalability:
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const router = express.Router();

router.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Users list');
});

module.exports = router;
```

3. Use `app.use` to load the route module:
```javascript
const userRoutes = require('./userRoutes');
app.use('/api', userRoutes);
```

