Steps to implement RBAC in a Node.js app:

1. Define roles and permissions:
```javascript
const roles = ['admin', 'user'];
const permissions = {
  admin: ['read', 'write', 'delete'],
  user: ['read']
};
```

2. Create middleware to check user role and permissions:
```javascript
const checkPermission = (role, permission) => {
  return permissions[role] && permissions[role].includes(permission);
};
```

3. Apply middleware in routes:
```javascript
app.get('/admin', (req, res) => {
  if (checkPermission(req.user.role, 'delete')) {
    res.send('Access granted to delete');
  } else {
    res.status(403).send('Forbidden');
  }
});
```

4. Ensure user roles are assigned correctly during authentication.

 Reference: https://expressjs.com/en/starter/basic-routing.html

