Steps to implement JWT in Node.js:

1. Install `jsonwebtoken` package:
```bash
npm install jsonwebtoken
```

2. Create and sign a token on successful login:
```javascript
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');

const token = jwt.sign({ userId: 1 }, 'your-secret-key', { expiresIn: '1h' });

res.json({ token });
```

3. Verify the token for protected routes:
```javascript
const verifyToken = (req, res, next) => {
  const token = req.headers['authorization']?.split(' ')[1];
  if (!token) return res.status(403).send('Token required');

  jwt.verify(token, 'your-secret-key', (err, decoded) => {
    if (err) return res.status(401).send('Invalid token');
    req.userId = decoded.userId;
    next();
  });
};
```

4. Protect routes using middleware:
```javascript
app.get('/protected', verifyToken, (req, res) => {
  res.send('Protected content');
});
```

 Reference: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/nodejs-jwt-expressjs

