Steps to handle exceptions in Node.js:

1. Use `try-catch` for synchronous errors:
```javascript
try {
  throw new Error('Something went wrong');
} catch (err) {
  console.error(err.message);
}
```

2. Handle asynchronous errors using callback pattern:
```javascript
fs.readFile('nonexistent_file.txt', (err, data) => {
  if (err) {
    console.error(err.message);
  }
  else {
    console.log(data);
  }
});
```

3. Use `process.on('uncaughtException')` for unhandled errors:
```javascript
process.on('uncaughtException', (err) => {
  console.error('Uncaught exception:', err.message);
});
```

 Reference: https://nodejs.org/en/docs/guides/blocking-vs-non-blocking/

