Steps to use `Promise` in JavaScript:

1. Create a new Promise:
```javascript
let promise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
  let success = true;
  if (success) {
    resolve('Operation successful');
  } else {
    reject('Operation failed');
  }
});
```

2. Handle the result of the Promise:
```javascript
promise.then((result) => {
  console.log(result);
}).catch((error) => {
  console.error(error);
});
```

3. Use `async-await` to handle Promises in a more readable way:
```javascript
async function example() {
  try {
    let result = await promise;
    console.log(result);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error);
  }
}
example();
```

 Reference: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise

