Steps to sort an array in JavaScript:

1. Sort an array of numbers:
```javascript
let numbers = [5, 2, 9, 1, 5, 6];
numbers.sort((a, b) => a - b);
console.log(numbers); // [1, 2, 5, 5, 6, 9]
```

2. Sort an array of strings:
```javascript
let strings = ['banana', 'apple', 'cherry'];
strings.sort();
console.log(strings); // ['apple', 'banana', 'cherry']
```

3. Sort an array of objects by a property:
```javascript
let people = [{name: 'Alice'}, {name: 'Bob'}, {name: 'Charlie'}];
people.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
console.log(people);
```

 Reference: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/sort

