Steps to implement multi-threading in Java:

1. Create a class that extends the Thread class or implements the Runnable interface.
2. Override the run() method to define the code that will be executed by the thread.
3. Instantiate the thread class and call the start() method.
4. Optionally, use Thread.join() to wait for the threads to finish before continuing.

```java
class MyThread extends Thread {
  public void run() {
    System.out.println("Thread running");
  }
}

public class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    MyThread t = new MyThread();
    t.start();
  }
}
```

