Steps to create a basic authentication system in Node.js:

1. Install necessary packages:
```bash
npm install express basic-auth
```

2. Create a middleware function to check authentication:
```javascript
const basicAuth = require('basic-auth');

app.use((req, res, next) => {
  const user = basicAuth(req);
  if (!user || user.name !== 'admin' || user.pass !== 'password') {
    res.status(401).send('Unauthorized');
  } else {
    next();
  }
});
```

3. Use this middleware to protect your routes.

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/basic-auth

