Steps to use WebSockets in Node.js for real-time communication:

1. Install the `ws` package:
```bash
npm install ws
```
2. Create a WebSocket server:
```javascript
const WebSocket = require('ws');
const wss = new WebSocket.Server({ port: 8080 });

wss.on('connection', (ws) => {
  console.log('Client connected');
  ws.send('Hello from server!');
  ws.on('message', (message) => {
    console.log('Received: ' + message);
  });
});
```
3. Connect to the WebSocket server from a client (browser or Node.js):
```javascript
const ws = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:8080');
ws.onmessage = (event) => {
  console.log('Received: ' + event.data);
};
```
4. You can use WebSockets for real-time features like live chat and notifications.

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/ws

