Steps to perform a database migration in MongoDB:

1. Use a migration tool like `migrate-mongo`:
```bash
npm install migrate-mongo
```
2. Initialize the migration project:
```bash
npx migrate-mongo init
```
3. Create a new migration file:
```bash
npx migrate-mongo create add-user-schema
```
4. Define the migration in the file:
```javascript
module.exports = {
  up: async function(db, client) {
    // Perform migration logic (e.g., adding a new field to a collection)
    await db.collection('users').updateMany({}, { $set: { newField: 'value' } });
  },
  down: async function(db, client) {
    // Reverse migration logic
    await db.collection('users').updateMany({}, { $unset: { newField: '' } });
  }
};
```
5. Run the migration:
```bash
npx migrate-mongo up
```
6. Verify that the migration was successful by checking the collection.

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/migrate-mongo

