Steps to use Redis for session management in Node.js:

1. Install `redis` and `express-session` packages:
```bash
npm install redis express-session
```
2. Set up Redis client and session middleware:
```javascript
const redis = require('redis');
const session = require('express-session');
const RedisStore = require('connect-redis')(session);

const client = redis.createClient();

app.use(session({
  store: new RedisStore({ client }),
  secret: 'mysecret',
  resave: false,
  saveUninitialized: false,
  cookie: { secure: true }
}));
```
3. Use session in your application:
```javascript
app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  if (!req.session.views) {
    req.session.views = 1;
  } else {
    req.session.views++;
  }
  res.send(`Views: ${req.session.views}`);
});
```
4. Redis can handle high throughput and large amounts of session data.

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/connect-redis

