Steps to create a REST API in Node.js using Express:

1. Install Express:
```bash
npm install express
```
2. Set up your Express server:
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const port = 3000;

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello World');
});

app.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${port}`);
});
```
3. Create API endpoints to handle CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete):
```javascript
// Create
app.post('/api/users', (req, res) => {
  res.send('User created');
});

// Read
app.get('/api/users', (req, res) => {
  res.json([{ id: 1, name: 'John Doe' }]);
});

// Update
app.put('/api/users/:id', (req, res) => {
  res.send('User updated');
});

// Delete
app.delete('/api/users/:id', (req, res) => {
  res.send('User deleted');
});
```
4. Your API is now ready to perform CRUD operations.

 Reference: https://expressjs.com/en/starter/basic-routing.html

