Steps to implement pagination in Express.js with MongoDB:

1. Install necessary packages:
```bash
npm install mongoose express
```
2. Set up a MongoDB connection using Mongoose:
```javascript
const mongoose = require('mongoose');

mongoose.connect('mongodb://localhost/mydb', { useNewUrlParser: true, useUnifiedTopology: true });
```
3. Create a model for your data:
```javascript
const Item = mongoose.model('Item', new mongoose.Schema({
  name: String,
  description: String
}));
```
4. Implement pagination in your route:
```javascript
app.get('/items', async (req, res) => {
  const page = parseInt(req.query.page) || 1;
  const pageSize = parseInt(req.query.pageSize) || 10;
  const items = await Item.find().skip((page - 1) * pageSize).limit(pageSize);
  res.json(items);
});
```
5. You can now paginate your data easily with MongoDB and Express.

 Reference: https://mongoosejs.com/docs/pagination.html

