Steps to implement caching in Node.js using Redis:

1. Install Redis and the Redis client for Node.js:
```bash
npm install redis
```
2. Set up Redis client:
```javascript
const redis = require('redis');
const client = redis.createClient();
client.on('error', (err) => console.log('Error ' + err));
```
3. Cache data in Redis:
```javascript
const getCachedData = (key) => {
  client.get(key, (err, data) => {
    if (data) {
      return JSON.parse(data);
    }
    return null;
  });
};
```
4. Store data in Redis cache:
```javascript
const storeInCache = (key, value) => {
  client.setex(key, 3600, JSON.stringify(value));
};
```
5. You can now use caching in your Node.js app to store frequently accessed data.

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/redis

