Steps to implement pagination in MongoDB with Node.js:

1. Install Mongoose:
```bash
npm install mongoose
```
2. Define a Mongoose model and query with pagination:
```javascript
const User = mongoose.model('User', userSchema);

const getPaginatedUsers = async (page, limit) => {
  const users = await User.find()
    .skip((page - 1) * limit)
    .limit(limit);
  return users;
};
```
3. Set up pagination on a route:
```javascript
app.get('/users', async (req, res) => {
  const page = parseInt(req.query.page) || 1;
  const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit) || 10;
  const users = await getPaginatedUsers(page, limit);
  res.json(users);
});
```
4. Your MongoDB query will now return paginated results.

 Reference: https://mongoosejs.com/docs/api/query.html#query_Query-skip

