Steps to create an authentication system in Node.js:

1. Install necessary libraries:
```bash
npm install express bcryptjs jsonwebtoken```
2. Set up user registration with bcryptjs to hash passwords:
```javascript
const bcrypt = require('bcryptjs');

app.post('/register', async (req, res) => {
  const hashedPassword = await bcrypt.hash(req.body.password, 10);
  // Save hashedPassword to the database
});
```
3. Create a login endpoint to issue JSON Web Tokens (JWT):
```javascript
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');

app.post('/login', (req, res) => {
  const token = jwt.sign({ userId: user.id }, 'secretkey');
  res.json({ token });
});
```
4. Protect routes using middleware to verify JWT:
```javascript
const verifyToken = (req, res, next) => {
  const token = req.headers['authorization'];
  jwt.verify(token, 'secretkey', (err, decoded) => {
    if (err) return res.sendStatus(403);
    req.user = decoded;
    next();
  });
};
app.use(verifyToken);
```
5. Your authentication system is now set up with Node.js.

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/bcryptjs

