Steps to set up a static file server with Express.js:

1. Set up Express and serve static files:
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
app.use(express.static('public'));  // 'public' folder will contain static files

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server running on port 3000');
});
```
2. Place your static files (e.g., `index.html`, CSS, JS) in the `public` folder.
3. Now, clients can access the static files by visiting `http://localhost:3000/index.html` or any other file inside the `public` directory.
4. This is ideal for serving frontend assets in a Node.js web app.

 Reference: https://expressjs.com/en/starter/static-files.html

