Steps to use MongoDB with Express.js in a MERN stack:

1. Set up a Node.js server with Express:
```bash
npm install express
```
2. Install MongoDB and Mongoose for database interaction:
```bash
npm install mongoose
```
3. Connect to MongoDB from your Express app:
```javascript
const mongoose = require('mongoose');

mongoose.connect('mongodb://localhost:27017/mernapp', { useNewUrlParser: true, useUnifiedTopology: true })
  .then(() => console.log('Connected to MongoDB'))
  .catch((err) => console.error('Error:', err));
```
4. Define a Mongoose model:
```javascript
const Schema = mongoose.Schema;
const userSchema = new Schema({
  name: String,
  email: String
});
const User = mongoose.model('User', userSchema);
```
5. Use the model in Express routes to save and query data:
```javascript
app.post('/users', async (req, res) => {
  const user = new User(req.body);
  await user.save();
  res.send('User added');
});
```
6. This completes the integration of MongoDB with Express in the MERN stack.

 Reference: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Server-side/Express_Nodejs/mongoose

