Steps to handle asynchronous code in Node.js:

1. Use callbacks for asynchronous operations:
```javascript
fs.readFile('file.txt', (err, data) => {
  if (err) throw err;
  console.log(data);
});
```
2. Use promises for handling asynchronous code more cleanly:
```javascript
const readFile = (path) => {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    fs.readFile(path, (err, data) => {
      if (err) reject(err);
      resolve(data);
    });
  });
};
```
3. Use async/await to simplify promise handling:
```javascript
async function readFileAsync(path) {
  try {
    const data = await readFile(path);
    console.log(data);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(err);
  }
}
```
4. Asynchronous programming is essential for non-blocking operations in Node.js.

 Reference: https://nodejs.org/en/docs/guides/blocking-vs-non-blocking/

