Steps to validate user input in Node.js:

1. Use a validation library like `express-validator` for input validation:
```bash
npm install express-validator
```
2. Use `express-validator` to validate and sanitize input:
```javascript
const { body, validationResult } = require('express-validator');

app.post('/register',
  body('email').isEmail().withMessage('Invalid email').trim().escape(),
  body('password').isLength({ min: 6 }).withMessage('Password must be at least 6 characters'),
  (req, res) => {
    const errors = validationResult(req);
    if (!errors.isEmpty()) {
      return res.status(400).json({ errors: errors.array() });
    }
    res.send('User registered');
  });
```
3. Handle validation errors appropriately to give feedback to users.

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/express-validator

