Steps to manage sessions in Node.js:

1. Install the `express-session` middleware:
```bash
npm install express-session
```
2. Set up session middleware in your Express app:
```javascript
const session = require('express-session');

app.use(session({
  secret: 'your-secret-key',
  resave: false,
  saveUninitialized: true,
  cookie: { secure: true }
}));
```
3. Store user data in session:
```javascript
app.post('/login', (req, res) => {
  req.session.user = { id: '1234', name: 'John Doe' };
  res.send('User logged in');
});
```
4. Access session data on protected routes:
```javascript
app.get('/profile', (req, res) => {
  if (req.session.user) {
    res.send(`Welcome, ${req.session.user.name}`);
  } else {
    res.send('Please log in');
  }
});
```
5. Use session to manage user state across requests.

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/express-session

