Steps to manage component lifecycle in React using `useEffect`:

1. Run a side effect on component mount:
```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  // This runs when the component mounts
  console.log('Component mounted');
}, []);
```
2. Run a side effect on component update:
```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  // This runs when the component or any of its dependencies change
  console.log('Component updated');
}, [count]);
```
3. Clean up side effects when a component unmounts (like unsubscribing from an event):
```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  return () => {
    console.log('Component will unmount');
  };
}, []);
```
4. `useEffect` combines the behavior of `componentDidMount`, `componentDidUpdate`, and `componentWillUnmount` into one API.

 Reference: https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-effect.html

