Steps to secure a Node.js app with HTTPS:

1. Generate an SSL certificate (self-signed or from a CA):
```bash
openssl genpkey -algorithm RSA -out server-key.pem
openssl req -new -key server-key.pem -out server.csr
openssl x509 -req -in server.csr -signkey server-key.pem -out server-cert.pem
```
2. Set up HTTPS server in your Node.js app:
```javascript
const https = require('https');
const fs = require('fs');

const options = {
  key: fs.readFileSync('server-key.pem'),
  cert: fs.readFileSync('server-cert.pem')
};

https.createServer(options, (req, res) => {
  res.writeHead(200);
  res.end('Hello, HTTPS!');
}).listen(443);
```
3. Redirect HTTP to HTTPS for better security.

 Reference: https://nodejs.org/en/docs/guides/anatomy-of-an-http-transaction/#https

