Steps to implement rate limiting in an Express app:

1. Install `express-rate-limit` package:
```bash
npm install express-rate-limit
```
2. Create a rate limit middleware:
```javascript
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');

const limiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, // 15 minutes
  max: 100, // Limit each IP to 100 requests per windowMs
  message: 'Too many requests, please try again later.'
});

app.use(limiter);
```
3. Optionally, apply rate limiting to specific routes only:
```javascript
app.post('/login', limiter, (req, res) => {
  res.send('Login attempt');
});
```
4. Use a Redis store for distributed rate limiting if you're running multiple instances of your app.

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/express-rate-limit

