Steps to handle errors in Express middleware:

1. Create an error handling middleware function:
```javascript
function errorHandler(err, req, res, next) {
  console.error(err.stack);
  res.status(500).send('Something went wrong!');
}
```
2. Use the error handler middleware at the end of the middleware stack:
```javascript
app.use(errorHandler);
```
3. Pass errors to the error handler by calling `next(err)` in route handlers or other middleware:
```javascript
app.get('/error', (req, res, next) => {
  next(new Error('This is an error!'));
});
```
4. Optionally, use custom error classes for better error categorization.

 Reference: https://expressjs.com/en/guide/error-handling.html

