3. Use aggregation pipeline to perform complex queries:
```javascript
Product.aggregate([
  { $match: { category: 'Electronics' } },
  { $group: { _id: '$category', totalPrice: { $sum: '$price' } } },
  { $sort: { totalPrice: -1 } }
]).exec((err, result) => {
  console.log(result);
});
```

 Reference: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/aggregation/

