Steps to create a custom error handler in Express.js:

1. Define your error-handling middleware:
```javascript
function errorHandler(err, req, res, next) {
  console.error(err.stack);
  res.status(500).send('Something went wrong!');
}
```

2. Use the error handler middleware in your app:
```javascript
app.use(errorHandler);
```

3. You can also create specific error handlers for different error types, such as validation errors:
```javascript
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  if (err.name === 'ValidationError') {
    res.status(400).send('Validation failed');
  } else {
    next(err);
  }
});
```

 Reference: https://expressjs.com/en/guide/using-middleware.html#custom-error-handling

