Steps to implement file compression in Node.js:

1. Install `zlib` (built-in in Node.js) and `fs` modules:
```javascript
const zlib = require('zlib');
const fs = require('fs');
```

2. Compress a file:
```javascript
const input = fs.createReadStream('input.txt');
const output = fs.createWriteStream('input.txt.gz');
const compress = zlib.createGzip();
input.pipe(compress).pipe(output);
```

3. Decompress a file:
```javascript
const decompress = zlib.createGunzip();
const input = fs.createReadStream('input.txt.gz');
const output = fs.createWriteStream('output.txt');
input.pipe(decompress).pipe(output);
```

 Reference: https://nodejs.org/api/zlib.html

