Steps to handle errors in Node.js:

1. Use try-catch blocks for synchronous code:
```javascript
try {
  // Some code
} catch (err) {
  console.error('Error occurred:', err);
}
```

2. Handle asynchronous errors with `callback` pattern or Promises:
```javascript
fs.readFile('file.txt', 'utf8', (err, data) => {
  if (err) {
    console.error('Error occurred:', err);
  } else {
    console.log(data);
  }
});
```

3. Handle global unhandled errors by listening to the `uncaughtException` event:
```javascript
process.on('uncaughtException', (err) => {
  console.error('Unhandled error:', err);
});
```

 Reference: https://nodejs.org/api/process.html#process_event_uncaughtexception

