Steps to implement RBAC in Express:

1. Define roles and permissions:
```javascript
const roles = ['admin', 'user'];
const permissions = {
  admin: ['read', 'write', 'delete'],
  user: ['read']
};
```

2. Create a middleware to check the user's role and permissions:
```javascript
const checkPermission = (role, permission) => (req, res, next) => {
  if (!permissions[role].includes(permission)) {
    return res.status(403).send('Forbidden');
  }
  next();
};
```

3. Use the middleware in routes:
```javascript
app.post('/admin', checkPermission('admin', 'write'), (req, res) => {
  res.send('Admin route');
});
```

 Reference: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Role-based_access_control

