Steps to send an email in Node.js using `nodemailer`:

1. Install `nodemailer` package:
```bash
npm install nodemailer
```

2. Create a transporter with SMTP settings:
```javascript
const nodemailer = require('nodemailer');
const transporter = nodemailer.createTransport({
  service: 'gmail',
  auth: {
    user: 'your-email@gmail.com',
    pass: 'your-email-password'
  }
});
```

3. Define email options and send email:
```javascript
const mailOptions = {
  from: 'your-email@gmail.com',
  to: 'recipient@example.com',
  subject: 'Test Email',
  text: 'Hello from Node.js'
};
transporter.sendMail(mailOptions, (error, info) => {
  if (error) {
    console.log('Error:', error);
  } else {
    console.log('Email sent:', info.response);
  }
});
```

 Reference: https://www.npmjs.com/package/nodemailer

