Steps to secure your Node.js application with HTTPS:

1. Install `https` module:
```bash
npm install https
```

2. Set up an HTTPS server with a valid SSL certificate:
```javascript
const https = require('https');
const fs = require('fs');

const options = {
  key: fs.readFileSync('private.key'),
  cert: fs.readFileSync('certificate.crt')
};

https.createServer(options, (req, res) => {
  res.writeHead(200);
  res.end('Hello HTTPS');
}).listen(3000);
```

3. Redirect HTTP traffic to HTTPS:
```javascript
const http = require('http');
http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.writeHead(301, { Location: `https://${req.headers.host}${req.url}` });
  res.end();
}).listen(80);
```

 Reference: https://nodejs.org/dist/latest-v16.x/docs/api/https.html

