The `bind()` method is used to create a new function that, when called, has its `this` value set to a specific value.

This is particularly useful when you want to pass a function as a callback, but ensure that `this` refers to a particular object.

Example:
```javascript
const person = { name: 'John' };
const greet = function() {
  console.log('Hello, ' + this.name);
};

const greetPerson = greet.bind(person);
greetPerson(); // Output: 'Hello, John'
```

 Reference: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/bind

