To handle errors in asynchronous code:

1. Use try-catch blocks with `async/await`:
```javascript
try {
  const data = await fetchData();
} catch (err) {
  console.log('Error:', err);
}
```

2. Use `.catch()` with promises:
```javascript
fetchData().catch(err => {
  console.log('Error:', err);
});
```

3. Handle errors in callback functions:
```javascript
fs.readFile('file.txt', (err, data) => {
  if (err) {
    console.log('Error reading file:', err);
  } else {
    console.log('File data:', data);
  }
});
```

 Reference: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Guide/Control_flow_and_error_handling

